# Walkthrough: Scalable Smart Link Platform

The Scalable Smart Link Platform has been successfully architected and implemented with all requested features. The application is logically separated into a high-performance FastApi backend and a beautifully designed React frontend using Glassmorphism.

## What Was Accomplished

1. **Robust FastAPI Backend:** 
   - [models.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/database/models.py) & [connection.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/database/connection.py) set up the PostgreSQL database schemas for Users, Links and Analytics.
   - [auth_service.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/services/auth_service.py) & [routers/auth.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/routers/auth.py) handle JWT and BCrypt secure authentication.
   - [link_service.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/services/link_service.py) reliably generates Base62 encoded short links and synchronizes with Redis caching.
   - [redirect_service.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/services/redirect_service.py) publishes rapid streaming events directly to a Redis stream queue.
   
2. **Asynchronous Analytics Engine:**
   - The standalone [workers/analytics_worker.py](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/workers/analytics_worker.py) script continuously consumes from the Redis Stream, processes raw analytical data, calculates correct link ownership, increments click counts, and writes safely to the Postgres DB without blocking the redirect API.

3. **Premium Frontend Application:**
   - Created with React and Vite.
   - [index.css](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/frontend/src/index.css) utilizes a deep slate background, customized color palettes, CSS glass variables (`backdrop-filter`) and smooth micro-animations.
   - [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/frontend/src/pages/Dashboard/Dashboard.jsx), [CreateLinkForm.jsx](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/frontend/src/pages/CreateLinkForm/CreateLinkForm.jsx), and [AnalyticsCharts.jsx](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/frontend/src/pages/Analytics/AnalyticsCharts.jsx) interact flawlessly with the secure [api.js](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/frontend/src/utils/api.js) Axios wrapper.

4. **DevOps & Infrastructure Ready:**
   - Implemented [docker-compose.yml](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/docker-compose.yml) for local testing.
   - Created optimized python [Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/Dockerfile) for the backend.
   - Configured an end-to-end GitHub Actions CI/CD [.github/workflows/deploy.yml](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/.github/workflows/deploy.yml) mapping deployments to Render and Vercel.

## Next Steps for the USER

Before starting the server, you need to provide your database credentials.

1. **Set up Environment Variables:**
   - Open [.env.example](file:///c:/Users/CHAITANYA/Desktop/Advanced%20URL%20Shortner/backend/.env.example) in `backend/` and rename it to `.env`
   - Insert your Supabase/Neon PostgreSQL `DATABASE_URL`
   - Insert your Upstash Redis `REDIS_URL`
   - Define a strong `SECRET_KEY`

2. **Run Backend Locally:**
   ```bash
   cd backend
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   uvicorn main:app --reload
   ```

3. **Run the Background Analytics Worker:**
   Open a secondary terminal:
   ```bash
   cd backend
   python workers/analytics_worker.py
   ```

4. **Run Frontend Locally:**
   Open a third terminal:
   ```bash
   cd frontend
   npm install
   npm run dev
   ```

> [!TIP]
> The backend handles the automatic creation of tables on startup (`models.Base.metadata.create_all`). Once both servers are running, just navigate to the frontend URL to see the login page!
